Business Development
Morgan McKinley
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client, a major competitor in the interior Fit Out construction market are searching for an enthusiastic self motivated Business Development Manager to be based in Dubai.
Reporting to the General Manager you will be responsible for;
•	Prospect for potential new clients and turn this into increased business.
•	Plan approaches and pitches.
•	Build relationships with new clients.
•	Enhance existing relationships.
•	Forecast sales targets and ensure they are met by the sales team.
•	Track and record activity on accounts and help to close deals to meet these targets.
•	Identify opportunities for campaigns, distribution channels that will lead to an increase in sales.
•	Present to and consult with mid and senior level management on business trends with a view to developing new projects, services and distribution channels.
•	Attend Interior Fit Out functions and provide feedback and information on market and creative trends.
•	Work with image licensing sales teams and other internal colleagues to meet customer needs.
REQUIREMENTS
Requirements:
Candidate should meet the below criteria as a minimum:
•Our client have specified a EUROPEAN candidate is desired
•Extensive Fit Out experience within the Middle East
• Exceptional communication skills
•Degree educated is desired
•Bilingual English and Arabic is an advantage
•A proven track record of winning business
An attractive salary package will be negotiated dependent on experience.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
In November 2010, GCC specialist recruiter, iQ selection came together with global professional recruitment consultancy Morgan McKinley, under the name Morgan McKinley.
With 24 offices globally, Morgan McKinley connects specialist talent with leading employers across multiple industries and disciplines. We work very closely with international corporates, top investment banks and local SMEs to provide those looking for their next career move with the best job opportunities.
From our Dubai office, we provide specialist recruitment expertise spanning Financial Services & Finance; Sales, Marketing & Support; and Technical sectors throughout the GCC region, with dedicated consultants delivering focused sector and local knowledge. In addition, we are fully committed to promoting the government’s Emiratisation policy.
